{{Infobox recurring event | name= New York Clown Theatre Festival | logo= | image= | caption= | location= [[Brooklyn]], New York, U.S. | years_active=9 years | founded= 2005 By Audrey Crabtree, Eric Davis, Devon Ludow and The Brick Theater | dates= September 5–28<ref>[http://www.bricktheater.com/clown Official site]</ref> 2014, | genre= Clown festival | attendance= | patron= | website= [http://www.bricktheater.com/clown bricktheater.com] }}
The '''New York Clown Theatre Festival''' is an annual festival of the art of clown, held at [[The Brick Theater]] in [[Brooklyn]], New York. Kicked off every year by a parade beginning in Union Square and heading on the L train to [[Williamsburg, Brooklyn|Williamsburg]], the festival opens with a huge indoor pie fight. Festival performers come from across the U.S. and the globe, including Australia, Brazil, Canada, [[Catalonia]], Denmark, France, Germany, Ireland, Italy, Mexico, New Zealand, Spain, Switzerland and Britain.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/03/theater/03mcel.html?scp=1&sq=CLOWN%20THEATER%20FESTIVAL&st=cse The New York Times]</ref><ref>[http://clowns-online.com/clown-festival.php clowns-online]</ref><ref>[http://nymag.com/arts/theater/shortlists/19365/ New York Magazine]</ref>
Clown luminaries, including [[Aitor Basauri]], [[Christopher Bayes]], [[Bob Berky]], [[Audrey Crabtree]], [[Dody DiSanto]], [[Ronlin Foreman]], [[Philippe (Gaulier)]], [[Bill Irwin]], [[Eric Davis (clown)|Eric Davis]], [[Sue Morrison]] [[Joan Schirle]], and [[David Shiner (clown)|David Shiner]] have appeared and also given workshops and lectures at the festival.<ref>http://www.broadwayworld.com/off-off-broadway/article/NY-Clown-Theatre-to-Present-AMUSE-BOUCHE-2013-at-The-Brick-918-28-20130917#</ref>
